---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "BC PNP Regional Priorities 2026: The Ultimate City Guide";
const description =
    "Complete guide to moving to Regional BC for immigration. Detailed profiles of Prince George, Kelowna, Nanaimo, and rural communities. Includes cost of living, hospitals, and school districts.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <article class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
            <header class="space-y-4 text-center">
                <div
                    class="inline-block bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-bold mb-4"
                >
                    Strategy Guide
                </div>
                <h1
                    class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight"
                >
                    BC PNP <span class="text-teal-600">Regional City Guide</span
                    >
                </h1>
                <p
                    class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
                >
                    Don't just move for points—move for a better life. This
                    guide breaks down the best regional communities for jobs,
                    families, and fast-tracked PR.
                </p>
            </header>

            <div
                class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm"
            >
                <h2>The Strategy: Why Leave Vancouver?</h2>
                <p>
                    The "Metro Vancouver" area (Area 1) is oversaturated.
                    Everyone applies there. As a result, the points needed to
                    get invited are extremely high (often >120 SIRS points).
                </p>
                <p>By moving just 2-4 hours away, you can:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Lower your Cut-off Score:</strong> Regional draws
                        often invite people with scores as low as 80.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Get Bonus Points:</strong> +15 to +25 points instantly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Save Money:</strong> Rent is often 50% cheaper.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>City Profile 1: Prince George (The Northern Capital)</h2>
                <p>
                    Prince George is the largest city in Northern BC and acts as
                    the service hub for the entire upper half of the province.
                </p>

                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose my-6">
                    <div
                        class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200"
                    >
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Key Stats</h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Population:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold">~80,000</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Points bonus:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold text-green-600"
                                    >+15 (Area 3)</span
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Avg 2-Bed Rent:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold">$1,450</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200"
                    >
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">
                            Top Employers
                        </h4>
                        <ul
                            class="text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-700"
                        >
                            <li>Northern Health Authority (UHNBC)</li>
                            <li>Canfor (Forestry)</li>
                            <li>UNBC (University)</li>
                            <li>CN Rail</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    <strong>Livability:</strong> It has a Costco, malls, and a university.
                    It feels like a real city, not a village. Winters are cold (-20°C
                    is common), but sunny.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>City Profile 2: Kelowna (The Okanagan)</h2>
                <p>
                    Famous for wineries, lakes, and hot summers. It is rapidly
                    becoming a tech hub.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 not-prose my-6">
                    <div
                        class="bg-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-indigo-200"
                    >
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-2">
                            Key Stats
                        </h4>
                        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Population:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold">~150,000</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Points bonus:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold text-green-600"
                                    >+10 (Area 2/3)</span
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex justify-between">
                                <span>Avg 2-Bed Rent:</span>
                                <span class="font-bold">$2,200</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="bg-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-indigo-200"
                    >
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-2">
                            Top Industries
                        </h4>
                        <ul
                            class="text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-indigo-800"
                        >
                            <li>Technology (Accelerate Okanagan)</li>
                            <li>Tourism & Hospitality</li>
                            <li>Healthcare (Kelowna General Hospital)</li>
                            <li>Agriculture</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> Kelowna is expensive ("Vancouver prices
                    without Vancouver wages"). Ensure you have a good job offer before
                    moving here.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>City Profile 3: Nanaimo (The Harbour City)</h2>
                <p>
                    Located on Vancouver Island, a 1.5-hour ferry ride from
                    Vancouver.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Bonus Points:</strong> +10.</li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Vibe:</strong> Laid back, ocean-front, very popular
                        with retirees and young families.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Jobs:</strong> Construction, Education (VIU), Health,
                        Retail.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>Area 4: The "Deep North" (Maximum Points)</h2>
                <p>
                    If you move to <strong>Fort St. John</strong>, <strong
                        >Dawson Creek</strong
                    >, or <strong>Terrace</strong>, you enter "Area 4".
                </p>
                <div
                    class="bg-green-100 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-200 my-6"
                >
                    <h3 class="font-black text-green-900 text-xl mb-2">
                        Why Fort St. John?
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-green-800">
                        It has the highest average wage in BC (due to Oil &
                        Gas).
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-green-900 font-bold">
                        <li>✔️ +25 Regional Points (Maximum)</li>
                        <li>✔️ ELSS Eligibility for ANY TEER 4/5 job</li>
                        <li>✔️ High Wages</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Family Guide: Moving with Kids</h2>
                <p>
                    Moving regionally is often better for families than
                    individuals.
                </p>

                <h3>School Districts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Smaller Class Sizes:</strong> Regional schools often
                        have better teacher-to-student ratios than Surrey or Vancouver.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Special Programs:</strong> French Immersion is available
                        in almost all major regional towns (Prince George, Kamloops,
                        Nanaimo).
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Childcare Availability</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Reality Check:</strong> Childcare shortages exist everywhere
                    in BC. However, waitlists in places like Castlegar or Quesnel
                    are typically 6-12 months, compared to 2-3 years in Vancouver.
                </p>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>Extended Regional Zone List</h2>
                <p>
                    Ensure your employer is physically located in one of these
                    zones.
                </p>
                <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
                    <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm border-collapse">
                        <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-white">
                            <tr>
                                <th class="p-3">Zone</th>
                                <th class="p-3">Bonus</th>
                                <th class="p-3"
                                    >Eligible Communities (Partial List)</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-200">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-3 font-bold">Area 1</td>
                                <td class="p-3">0</td>
                                <td class="p-3 text-slate-600"
                                    >Vancouver, Surrey, Burnaby, Richmond,
                                    Coquitlam, Langley, Delta, North Vancouver,
                                    West Vancouver, Port Moody, Port Coquitlam,
                                    White Rock, Pitt Meadows, Maple Ridge, Lions
                                    Bay, Bowen Island, Anmore, Belcarra.</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-teal-50">
                                <td class="p-3 font-bold">Area 2</td>
                                <td class="p-3">+5</td>
                                <td class="p-3 text-slate-600"
                                    >Squamish, Abbotsford, Mission, Chilliwack,
                                    Hope, Kent, Harrison Hot Springs.</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-teal-100">
                                <td class="p-3 font-bold">Area 3</td>
                                <td class="p-3">+15</td>
                                <td class="p-3 text-slate-600">
                                    <strong>Vancouver Island:</strong> Victoria, Nanaimo,
                                    Saanich, Langford, Campbell River, Courtenay,
                                    Comox, Parksville, Port Alberni, Duncan, Ladysmith.<br
                                    />
                                    <strong>Okanagan:</strong> Kelowna, West Kelowna,
                                    Kamloops, Vernon, Penticton, Lake Country, Salmon
                                    Arm, Summerland, Peachland, Merritt.<br />
                                    <strong>Sunshine Coast:</strong> Sechelt, Gibsons.
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-green-100">
                                <td class="p-3 font-bold">Area 4</td>
                                <td class="p-3 text-green-800 font-bold">+25</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 text-slate-600">
                                    <strong>North:</strong> Prince George, Fort St.
                                    John, Dawson Creek, Terrace, Prince Rupert, Kitimat,
                                    Smithers, Williams Lake, Quesnel.<br />
                                    <strong>Kootenays:</strong> Cranbrook, Nelson,
                                    Castlegar, Trail, Fernie, Invermere, Revelstoke,
                                    Golden.<br />
                                    <strong>Others:</strong> Powell River, Tofino,
                                    Ucluelet, Haida Gwaii, Tumbler Ridge.
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>Regional Success Stories</h2>

                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div
                        class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <div
                                class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-blue-700 font-bold text-xl"
                            >
                                1
                            </div>
                            <div class="ml-4">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">
                                    From Surrey to Smithers
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
                                    Profile: Retail Manager (TEER 2)
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 italic">
                            "I was stuck at 90 points in Surrey. I couldn't get
                            invited. I applied for a job at a grocery store in
                            Smithers (Area 4). Immediately, my score jumped to
                            115 (+25 points). I was invited in the very next
                            draw. The rent is $1200 for a whole house!"
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div
                        class="bg-white border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <div
                                class="w-12 h-12 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-green-700 font-bold text-xl"
                            >
                                2
                            </div>
                            <div class="ml-4">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">
                                    The Kelowna Tech Shift
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
                                    Profile: Software Engineer
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 italic">
                            "I wanted to live in a city, not a village. Kelowna
                            gave me the best of both worlds. I got +10 regional
                            points, plus I qualified for the Tech Stream. It was
                            a no-brainer."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

                <h2>Strategic FAQ</h2>

                <h3>Can I live in Vancouver and work in the region?</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>NO.</strong> BC PNP requires you to live within "commuting
                    distance" of your job. If your job is in Kelowna, you must live
                    in the Okanagan. Living in Vancouver and working remotely for
                    a Kelowna company counts as "Vancouver employment" (0 points).
                </p>

                <h3>What if I get laid off?</h3>
                <p>
                    If you lose your regional job, you lose your regional
                    points. If this happens <em>after</em> you are nominated, you
                    must immediately inform BC PNP. They may allow you to find another
                    job in the <em>same</em> region, but moving back to Vancouver
                    would void your nomination.
                </p>

                <h3>Do I need a car?</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>YES.</strong> Public transit in regional BC is limited.
                    In Vancouver, you can survive with a Compass Card. In Prince George
                    or Kelowna, a vehicle is essential for getting to work and buying
                    groceries, especially in winter.
                </p>

                <div
                    class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-600 to-teal-800 text-white p-8 rounded-2xl text-center mt-12"
                >
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">
                        Calculate Your Regional Score
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-teal-100 mb-6">
                        See how much your score jumps by changing your region.
                    </p>
                    <a
                        href="/bc-pnp-calculator"
                        class="inline-block bg-white text-teal-900 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-teal-50 transition-colors"
                    >
                        Try Calculator →
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
